### Response:
The solution to the first equation is:
begin{align}
7 + 3 times 5 - frac{8}{2} &= 7 + 15 - 4 
&= 18
end{align}
Using this result, we can solve the second equation as follows:
begin{align}
(text{?}) + 2 times 9 - frac{5}{5} &= 19 
(text{?}) + 18 - 1 &= 19 
(text{?}) &= 2
end{align}
Therefore, the missing number in the second equation is 2.

